posts.raw_content:
I miss 24 hour grocery stores and pharmacies.  I used to do my grocery shopping either late at night or early morning when there are less people, less traffic and cooler outside.  

Now, if I don't get there before they open I'm parked at the backend of nowhere and have to spend 30 minutes just waiting to check out.  Living in Texas, it warms up pretty damn quick.

I'm on call 24/7.  My hours vary.  Now that none of the actual pharmacies in my town stay open past 8pm, I no longer have the option of swinging by and picking up prescriptions at 2am as I'm heading out of town for a job.  I don't always have the option of going during normal business hours.

Finally, I hate the reliance we've developed on delivery services.  I'd rather do my own shopping.  But more infuriating is the fact that most of the drivers don't speak nor understand English.
